e teamwork/communication as a key factor. C has explicit positive crew atmosphere, while D has none and has moody/loner. That seems more critical. So we might shift to C.\n\nWe must weigh strengths and weaknesses. C's negatives: difficulty communicating, egocentric, not willing to further education. Those are significant but may be mitigated. D's negatives: moody, loner, arrogant, weak leadership. Those also affect crew. Which is worse? Both are interpersonal. But C has a positive crew atmosphere, indicating good teamwork despite communication difficulty. That seems to outweigh D's lack of any positive crew attribute.\n\nThus we should likely change vote to Candidate C.\n\nWe should also ask if any agent has any positive teamwork/communication info for D or A that we might have missed, to be thorough. But we already asked both agents and they said none. However we could ask agent_1 or agent_2 if they have any additional positive attributes for D regarding teamwork, communication, crew cooperation beyond what we have. But we already asked agent_2 about D and got none. We asked agent_1 about D? Yes, agent_1 responded earlier that no positive attributes for D. So we have that.\n\nThus we have all info. So we can finalize vote for C.\n\nWe need to produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE with reasoning and maybe ask any remaining question? Probably no need. We can just state reasoning and vote.\n\nNow produce final."}
